data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: Diagnostic Service 0x10, also known as Diagnostic Session Control (DSC), is a key feature in automotive diagnostics defined by the UDS (Unified Diagnostic Services) protocol under ISO 14229. This service enables communication between the diagnostic tool and a vehicle's electronic control units (ECUs) by transitioning the ECU into specific diagnostic modes, or "sessions."

data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value: Diagnostic Service 0x11, commonly known as ECU Reset, is a vital function within the UDS (Unified Diagnostic Services) protocol, as defined by ISO 14229. This service enables a diagnostic tool to request a reset of an ECU (Electronic Control Unit), allowing the system to reinitialize its software or recover from an error state.
